fields.name: FacebookLeads
fields.short_description: Facebook platform focused on advertising and interconnection of potential customers with businesses.
fields.description: Facebook platform that seeks to take advantage of the increase in the use of mobile telephony, allowing the user to register and receive information about the businesses and businesses of their interest.

fields.name: MySQL
fields.short_description: A relational database management system especially used in web development environments.
fields.description: MySQL is a relational database management system developed under a dual license GPL/Commercial License by Oracle Corporation and is considered the most popular open source database in the world, and one of the most popular in general with Oracle and Microsoft SQL Server, especially for web development environments.
fields.connection_help_text: Requirements: - MySQL database configured. - Connection data to database. - The server where the database is located must be accessible from the Internet.

fields.name: SugarCRM
fields.short_description: System for managing the relationship with customers (CRM).
fields.description: SugarCRM is a system for the management of the relationship with customers (CRM) based on LAMP (Linux-Apache-MySQL-PHP), developed by the company SugarCRM, Inc. located in Cupertino, California.

fields.name: MailChimp
fields.short_description: An email marketing service provider
fields.description: MailChimp started as a paid service and added a free version 8 years later. The company logo is a chimp, and humorous images of the subject are included on the site and in its communications.

fields.name: GoogleSpreadSheet
fields.short_description: Spreadsheet web service, made in AJAX technology.
fields.description: It is a web service of spreadsheets, made in AJAX technology. With it you can perform most of the functions left by spreadsheet applications of office programs, such as performing operations between cells with different types of functions (mathematical, financial, logical, dates, searches, statistics, with chains and informative), order columns, handle different sheets within each file, handle files of the xls and csv type, etc.

fields.name: PostgreSQL
fields.short_description: Is an object-oriented and free relational database management system.
fields.description: PostgreSQL is an object-oriented and free relational database management system, published under the PostgreSQL license, similar to BSD or MIT. Like many other open source projects, the development of PostgreSQL is not managed by a company or person, but is directed by a community of developers who work in a selfless, altruistic, free or supported by commercial organizations. This community is called the PGDG (PostgreSQL Global Development Group). PostgreSQL does not have a defect manager, making it very difficult to know the status of its defects.

fields.name: MSSQLServer
fields.short_description: Is a database management system of the relational model, developed by Microsoft.
fields.description: Microsoft SQL Server is a database management system of the relational model, developed by Microsoft. The development language used (by command line or through the graphical interface of Management Studio) is Transact-SQL (TSQL), an implementation of the ANSI standard of the SQL language, used to manipulate and recover data (DML), create tables and define relationships between them (DDL).

fields.name: Slack
fields.short_description: Team communication tool.
fields.description: Slack is a team communication tool created by Stewart Butterfield, Eric Costello, Cal Henderson, and Serguei Mourachov. Slack emerges as an internal tool used by the company Tiny Speck in the development of Glitch, an online game that is currently obsolete. Slack was launched in August 2013 and achieved a record of 8,000 customers in the first 24 hours.

fields.name: JIRA
fields.short_description: Online tool for managing project tasks.
fields.description: JIRA is an online tool for managing project tasks, tracking errors and incidents and for the operational management of projects. The tool was developed by the Australian company Atlassian. Initially Jira was used for software development, serving as support for the management of requirements, monitoring the development status and later for error management. Jira can be used for the management and improvement of processes, thanks to its functions for the organization of workflows.

fields.name: Bitbucket
fields.short_description: Web-based hosting service for projects that use the Mercurial and Git revision control system.
fields.description: Bitbucket is a web-based hosting service for projects that use the Mercurial and Git revision control system. Bitbucket offers commercial and free plans. It offers free accounts with an unlimited number of private repositories (which can have up to five users in the case of free accounts) since September 2010, private repositories are not displayed on the profile pages - if a user only has private deposits, the website will give the message "This user does not have repositories". The service is written in Python.

fields.name: GoogleForms
fields.short_description: Tool for the creation of Forms and Professional Reports for Your Company.
fields.description: With Google Forms create a new survey alone or with other users at the same time. Choose from various attractive predesigned themes or create your own. Analyze your results on Google Forms. Free Google application.

fields.name: Twitter
fields.short_description: Is a microblogging service that allows you to send short text messages
fields.description: The network allows you to send text messages of short length, with a maximum of 280 characters (originally 140), called tweets, which are displayed on the user's homepage. Users can subscribe to other users' tweets - this is called "follow" and subscribers are called "followers", "followers" and sometimes tweeps ('Twitter' + 'peeps', novice followers who have not yet they have made many tweets). By default, the messages are public, and can be broadcast privately by showing them only to certain followers. Users can tweet from the service's website, with official external applications (such as for smartphones), or through the Short Message Service (SMS) available in certain countries.While the service is free, access to it via SMS involves support rates set by the mobile phone provider.

fields.name: GetResponse
fields.short_description: Is an email marketing platform.
fields.description: GetResponse enables you to create a valuable marketing list of prospects, partners, and clients, so you can develop relationships with them and build a responsive and profitable customer base. It has the deliverability rate of 99.5%, to make sure your messages reach destination inboxes.

fields.name: GoogleContacts
fields.short_description: Is an online address book.
fields.description: Google Contacts is your online address book, integrated with Gmail, Calendar, Drive, and other Google products. Sync your contacts to all your devices and access them everywhere.

fields.name: SurveyMonkey
fields.short_description: Service that allows users to create online surveys.
fields.description: SurveyMonkey is a US company that allows users to create online surveys. The company's offices are located in Menlo Park, California and Portland, Oregon.

fields.name: GoogleCalendar
fields.short_description: Schedule and electronic calendar developed by Google.
fields.description: It allows you to synchronize it with Gmail contacts so we can invite you and share events. It is available from April 13, 2006. Although users are not required to have a Gmail account, they must have a Google Account to use the software.

fields.name: MercadoLibre
fields.short_description: Platform where users can sell both new and used products at a fixed price.
fields.description: MercadoLibre also has MercadoPago, a collection platform for sellers. Its headquarters are located in Buenos Aires, Argentina. According to The Nielsen Company more than 52,000 people generate all or most of their income selling through MercadoLibre and in 2009 more than 3 million people and companies sold at least one article through this medium.

fields.name: AmazonSellerCentral
fields.short_description: Platform created and operated by Amazon where individuals and businesses can market their goods.
fields.description: Since 2000, Selling on Amazon has been helping individuals and businesses increase sales and reach new customers. Today, more than 40% of Amazon's total unit sales come from third-party selection. All sellers can list products in more than 20 categories. Professional Sellers can apply to sell in at least 10 additional categories.

fields.name: PayU
fields.short_description: Provider of payment services.
fields.description: PayU is a leading provider of payment services with presence in 16 growth and emerging markets around the world.

fields.name: Gmail
fields.short_description: Email service with POP3 and free IMAP possibilities.
fields.description: It offers a storage capacity of 15 GB. Message filter, which has many options. Maximum size of each message (text and attachments) is 25 MB. encryption with SSL. The mail page can also be encrypted by SSL. Available for mobile devices.

fields.name: Ebay
fields.short_description: Site intended for the auction of products through the Internet.
fields.description: It is one of the pioneers in this type of transaction, having been founded in 1995. From 2002 until 2015, eBay has been the owner of PayPal.

fields.name: WooComerce
fields.short_description: Open source e-commerce plugin for WordPress.
fields.description: Designed for small and large online merchants with WordPress. Launched on September 27, 2011, the plugin quickly became popular for its simplicity to install and customize the database of products sold. WooCommerce has been adopted by more than 380,000 online retailers. It is used by a series of high traffic websites.

fields.name: Instagram
fields.short_description: Social network and application to upload photos and videos.
fields.description: Users can apply photographic effects such as filters, frames, thermal similarities, underlying areas in the concave bases, retro colors, and then share the photographs in the same social network or in others such as Facebook, Tumblr, Flickr and Twitter.

fields.name: Youtube
fields.short_description: Website dedicated to share videos.
fields.description: It hosts a variety of movie clips, television shows and music videos, as well as amateur content such as video blogs and YouTube Gaming.

fields.name: Vimeo
fields.short_description: Social network based on videos.
fields.description: The site allows to share and store digital videos for users to comment on the page of each of them. Users must be registered to upload videos, create their profile, upload avatars, comment and build favorite lists.

fields.name: ZohoCRM
fields.short_description: Administration and management application.
fields.description: It allows you to keep a contact list, things to do, manage user groups, among others.

fields.name: WunderList
fields.short_description: Cloud-based task management application.
fields.description: It allows users to manage their tasks from a smartphone, tablet, computer and smartwatch. Wunderlist is free; additional collaboration features are available in a paid version known as Wunderlist Pro.

fields.name: Evernote
fields.short_description: Cross-platform app designed for note taking, organizing, and archiving.
fields.description: The app allows users to create a "note" which can be a piece of formatted text, a full webpage or webpage excerpt, a photograph, a voice memo, or a handwritten "ink" note. Notes can also have file attachments. Notebooks can be added to a stack while notes can be sorted into a notebook, tagged, annotated, edited, given comments, searched, and exported as part of a notebook.

fields.name: Salesforce
fields.short_description: CRM solution in the cloud.
fields.description: Salesforce Is Fully Cloud-Based As mentioned above, basing a CRM solution in the cloud means that users can access its full functionality, without having to install costly in-house hardware or computer servers. No hardware means you’ll be up and running and positively impacting your business in no time at all.

fields.name: Vtiger
fields.short_description: Online customer relationship management software.
fields.description: Make better decisions with a holistic customer view that integrates information from marketing, sales, support, purchasing and more, collaboratively manage the delivery of customer projects with contact and opportunity integrated project management, manage the end-to-end sales process, with quotes, invoices, inventory and web-based payments against invoices.

fields.name: ProsperWorks
fields.short_description: CRM designed to help every salesperson excel at their job.
fields.description: ProsperWorks is the CRM for G Suite, so it seamlessly integrates with Google Sheets, Docs, Slides, Calendar, Inbox and Gmail, so using your CRM is just as easy as the tools you already use everyday. Was built using Google’s material design principles so it looks and feels exactly like G Suite. ProsperWorks fits right into your email so once you download the Gmail or Inbox Chrome Extension, you never have to leave your inbox.

fields.name: HubSpot
fields.short_description: CRM from Hubspot.
fields.description: The CRM product tracks and manages interactions between a company and its customers and prospects. It enables companies to forecast revenue, measure sales team productivity, and report on revenue sources. The software as a service product is free and integrates with Gmail, G Suite, Microsoft Office for Windows, and other software.

fields.name: PipeDrive
fields.short_description: A sales customer relationship management (CRM).
fields.description: Pipedrive is a cloud-based sales software company based in Tallinn, Estonia and New York City, New York. It is the maker of the web application and mobile app Pipedrive, a sales customer relationship management (CRM) tool for small and medium-sized businesses.

fields.name: DynamicCRM
fields.short_description: Customer relationship management software package developed by Microsoft.
fields.description: The product focuses mainly on Sales, Marketing, and Service (help desk) sectors, but Microsoft has been marketing Dynamics CRM as an XRM platform and has been encouraging partners to use its proprietary (.NET based) framework to customize it. It is part of the Microsoft Dynamics family of business applications.

fields.name: FreshDesk
fields.short_description: Support ticket system.
fields.description: Easy to use, quick to configure with multichannel support.

fields.name: AgileCRM
fields.short_description: Customer relationship management software.
fields.description: known for offering fully integrated sales, marketing and service automation solution for small businesses.

fields.name: GitLab
fields.short_description: Web-based Git repository manager.
fields.description: Has wiki and issue tracking features, using an open source license, developed by GitLab Inc.

fields.name: Shopify
fields.short_description: E-commerce platform.
fields.description: Especially for online stores and retail point-of-sale systems.

fields.name: Dropbox
fields.short_description: File hosting service.
fields.description: Dropbox offers cloud storage, file synchronization, personal cloud, and client software.

fields.name: Magento
fields.short_description: Open-source e-commerce platform written in PHP.
fields.description: Magento Community Edition, is an open-source eCommerce platform. Developers can implement the core files and extend its functionality by adding new plug-in modules provided by other developers.

fields.name: Asana
fields.short_description: Web and mobile application designed to help teams track their work.
fields.description: It focuses on allowing users to manage projects and tasks online without the use of email. Each team can create a workspace. Workspaces contain projects, and projects contain tasks. In each task, users can add notes, comments, attachments, and tags. Users can follow projects and tasks and, when the state of a project or task changes, followers get updates about the changes in their inboxes.

fields.name: Mandrill
fields.short_description: Transactional email API for MailChimp users.
fields.description: It's reliable, powerful, and ideal for sending data-driven emails, including targeted e-commerce and personalized one-to-one messages.

fields.name: ActiveCampaign
fields.short_description: Integrated email marketing, marketing automation, and small business CRM.
fields.description: Complete sales automation, manage and grow your list of contacts and capture more leads than ever before.

fields.name: TypeForm
fields.short_description: SaaS that makes very flexible, customized forms.
fields.description: Things like business forms, surveys, quizzes, product feedback, contest, landing page, test, and payment forms are all possible with Typeform. The customizations available far exceed what’s available with Google Forms (but rivals SurveyMonkey, for example) and that may be too much for your needs. All your forms can be found on the dashboard when you sign in, so you can keep everything organized.

fields.name: InfusionSoft
fields.short_description: E-mail marketing and sales platform for small businesses.
fields.description: InfusionSoft offers an integrated email marketing platform designed for small businesses with fewer than 25 employees. Specific features of the platform include lead scoring, web tracking, and social media tools.

fields.name: OdooCRM
fields.short_description: CRM software from Odoo ERP.
fields.description: Get accurate forecasts, automate activities based on your sales guide: calls, meetings, mailing and budgets. Real-time summary. Real-time messaging to improve collaboration.

fields.name: Batchbook
fields.short_description: Small business CRM solution.
fields.description: Easy Start, available on mobile, Automate all the little tasks – think recurring to-dos and routine emails – and add some extra time back into your day.

fields.name: ActEssentials
fields.short_description: Customer relationship management (CRM) software application.
fields.description: Used to keep track of client and prospect details in a single database that can be shared by multiple users. It integrates with Microsoft Word, Excel, Outlook, Google Contacts, Gmail and other popular applications in order to generate and track communications with the contacts maintained in ACT!.

fields.name: NimbleCRM
fields.short_description: Small business  CRM.
fields.description: Get the key benefits of Enterprise CRM to grow your business without the cost and complexity. Nimble delivers Contact Management, Sales and Marketing automation, people and company business intelligence, social listening and engagement and mobile/browser apps.

fields.name: Webhook
fields.short_description: Generic webhook implementation.
